<div class="recipe">
<p>Don't be fooled by its simplicity. This yogurt parfait will quickly become one your most popular concoctions to throw together. With just a few simple ingredients, you can create a quick, healthy, and tasty snack! All of these ingredients can easily be found wherever you shop and will last for a long time if stored properly.</p>
<p>While we recommend using a simple vanilla, low-fat yogurt, you really can use anything you want. Greek yogurt is a great choice if you are looking for a lower calorie option. If you are craving all that this dish has to offer, go ahead for the full-fat, sweetend variety (we won't judge!). Feel free to use a yogurt that already has a flavouring as well - if you do so, you may want to opt out of adding your own fruit as that may overload it.</p>
<p>Our granola topping will stay crispy, even after being left in the yogurt for some time. The heterogeniety offered by the crispy oats and the luxuriously smooth yogurt creates something that is truly delectable.</p>
<p>We decided to go all out with the fruit filling, as we prefer the texture of it after it has been cooked down. However, if you are looking to save time, you can simply use them in their raw form.</p>
<p>This yummy parfait will keep fresh for days, just make sure to keep it cold!</p>

