<div class="ingredients">
    <h3><strong>Ingredients</strong></h3>
    <ul>
        <li>4 cups vanilla low-fat yogurt</li>
        <li>1.5 cups fresh or frozen fruit (we recommend any type of berry)</li>
        <li><h6>Granola (or you can use 1.5 cups of storebought granola)</h6></li>
        <ul>
            <li>1 cup rolled oats</li>
            <li>1/2 cup chopped, raw nuts (we like almonds or pecans)</li>
            <li>1/2 teaspoon ground cinnamon</li>
            <li>1/4 cup melted coconut oil</li>
            <li>1/4 cup honey or maple syrup</li>
            <li>1/2 teaspoon vanilla extract</li>
            <li>salt, to taste</li>
        </ul>
    </ul>

    <h3><strong>Directions</strong></h3>
    Continue to step 6 if not making homemade granola

    <ol>
        <li>Preheat oven to 350F and line a large baking sheet with parchment or wax paper.</li>
        <li>In a medium bowl, combine the oats, nuts, cinnamon, and salt.</li>
        <li>In a separate bowl, mix the honey or maple syrup, melted coconut oil, vanilla. Then, pour into the bowl with the oats and mix well.</li>
        <li>Spread the oats mixture evenly over the prepared baking sheet.</li>
        <li>Bake for 20-25 minutes, or until golden brown. Let cool completely before proceeding.</li>
        <li>While the granola is cooling, prepare your fruit. If using raw fruit, you may want to slice it to more bitesized pieces. If you are cooking your fruit, bring a little bit of water to a boil over medium high heat and place your fruit inside the pot. Cook until the fruit softens conssiderable and a thick syrup begins to form. Set aside.</li>
        <li>Get a sizaeble, airtight container, and begin layering your granola, fruit and yogurt. The more layers you make, the more of each you will get in each bite!</li>
        <li>Store in a cold place until ready to eat. Enjoy!</li>
    </ol>
</div>
</div>





